      • convertPmmlWithErrors

        public org.nd4j.linalg.primitives.Pair<Map<Integer,Integer>,List<? extends Map<org.dmg.pmml.FieldName,?>>> convertPmmlWithErrors(org.datavec.api.transform.schema.Schema schema,
                                                                                                                                 io.vertx.core.json.JsonArray jsonArray,
                                                                                                                                 DataPipelineErrorHandler dataPipelineErrorHandler)
        Description copied from interface: JsonArrayConverter
        Convert a json array of arrays to the proper format for pmml. PMML expects a list of named tuples where each name is a FieldName representing a column in the input. This returns a mapping of original indices to the output indices. If there are no errors,mappings should be 1 to 1. If there were errors, the map is used to find what rows in the output (the second part of the pair) map to the original input rows.
        Specified by:
        convertPmmlWithErrors in interface JsonArrayConverter
        Parameters:
        schema - the inputSchema for the input
        jsonArray - the array of arrays to use
        dataPipelineErrorHandler - the DataPipelineErrorHandler when an error is encountered in the conversion step
        Returns:
        a map of the original inputs to the output rows, and the list of converted inputs in pmml format

        Description copied from interface: JsonArrayConverter
        Convert a json array of arrays to ArrowWritableRecordBatch. This returns a mapping of original indices to the output indices. If there are no errors,mappings should be 1 to 1. If there were errors, the map is used to find what rows in the output (the second part of the pair) map to the original input rows.

      • convert

        public org.datavec.arrow.recordreader.ArrowWritableRecordBatch convert(org.datavec.api.transform.schema.Schema schema,
                                                                       io.vertx.core.json.JsonArray jsonArray)
        Given a Schema transform the given input (an array of json objects) to an ArrowWritableRecordBatch for use with INDArray based pipelines (usually dl4j). Note that since index matters for this conversion (due to INDArray being index based) - internally, a inputSchema permutation happens to match the indices appropriate for use with the given inputSchema
        Specified by:
        convert in interface JsonArrayConverter
        Parameters:
        schema - the input inputSchema
        jsonArray - an array of json objects
        Returns:
        an ArrowWritableRecordBatch for use with conversion to INDArray
